programme.title: Eclectic Bohemian
programme.desc: Aspiring artist Akemi has left a corporate job to pursue her dream as a visionary artist, but she struggles with personal style and craves her parents' approval. Enter Stacy and Clinton, ready to create a bold, artsy look that truly reflects her creative spirit. Together, they empower Akemi to embrace her vibrant identity, boosting her confidence to thrive as the artist she was meant to be.

programme.title: Breaking Gender Norms
programme.desc: Clinton and Stacy take on their most exciting challenge yet with Alan, a recently transitioned trans man seeking a bold, androgynous style. After years of prioritizing comfort over self-expression, Alan is ready to embrace a look that defies traditional norms. Together, they craft a style that brings Alan a true joy that is uniquely his own, breaking the rules of fashion along the way.

programme.title: Parties and Holiday Feasts
programme.desc: It’s a party this week at America’s Test Kitchen! The 6 remaining cooks compete in challenges revolving around party food. The Task dares them to make an appetizer version of popular ATK main courses. Then Jeannie recruits the cooks’ own family members to bring the holidays to the Test Kitchen. Chef Joe Sasto joins judges Dan Souza and Julia Collin Davison in an emotional and celebratory episode.

programme.title: It’s an Abbondanza!
programme.desc: After a surprising test with no elimination, 6 cooks still remain. This week, the Task is to create, style and photograph a gift basket with a unique flavor profile. The winner gets a secret advantage! Next, we're going around the world in the Test with three-dish cuisine-themed food towers. Comedian Punkie Johnson guests.

programme.title: I’m on a Boat!
programme.desc: We’re down to the Final Five and the competition is fierce. This time, the cooks are going on a field trip! After spending a wonderful morning at Island Creek, the cooks must prepare two cooked oyster dishes in the Task Challenge. For the Test Challenge, the cooks are asked to impress guest judge Vivian Tu with their use of expensive ingredients and fine dining cuisine skills.

programme.title: Put Everything on the Table
programme.desc: Today in the Test Kitchen, the final four cooks have four hours to put together a cohesive, three-course meal. The catch: they must include one affordable cut of meat. Guest Richard Blais joins judges Dan Souza, Jack Bishop, and Elle Simone Scott in deciding which three cooks will make it to the finale, and who will be saying goodbye to the Test Kitchen for the final time.

programme.title: The Final Interview
programme.desc: It all comes down to this. The three remaining cooks must impress the judges as they prepare two dishes that represent their cookbook’s theme. Then, they produce a photo shoot of their dishes before doing a live 7-minute demo alongside Julia on the ATK stage. Finally, our cooks must pitch the judges why they should join the ATK team. In the end, one winner is crowned!

programme.title: Das Boat - April Vokey and Oliver Ngy Tackle a Notoriously Complex Bass Fishery in Florida
programme.desc: Lake Okeechobee‚ Florida‚ inland sea of freshwater, grass, and largemouth bass. Das Boat dives deep into Florida with a Candian and a Californian. April Vokey meets up with big bass expert Oliver Ngy and they try to figure out one of the most notoriously complex and rewarding bass fisheries in the country. They discuss the iconography of Okeechobee, America‚ obsession with bass, glitter boats, and the founders of Captains for Clean Water explain Florida‚ water quality problems.

programme.title: Das Boat - Frank Smethurst and Mustache Rob Hit Up the Savannah River in Augusta, Georgia
programme.desc: Frank Smethurst and Mustache Rob circle back to some of their old favorite stomping grounds on the Savannah River in Augusta, Georgia. They catch some of the many native sport fish in this archetypical southern river, and set their sights on the east coast‚ most sought after migratory game fish‚ stripers. Along the way, Das Boat gets a major upgrade, and they discuss the Georgia-South Carolina rivalry, southern roots, Bartram‚ Bass, and the intertwined history of Augusta and the Savannah River.

programme.title: Das Boat - Frank and Rob Are Back on the Savannah River Huntin' Catfish and Gar
programme.desc: Mustache Rob and Frank are back on the Savannah River in Georgia, headed 50+ miles downstream into water that they haven't seen before. It‚ an exploratory mission, though the Savannah is far from wilderness, and Rob and Frank‚ journey is more National Lampoon than Heart of Darkness. At the terminus of their trip waits Wade Plantation and some heaping platefuls of southern hospitality. All Rob and Frank have to do is bring some catfish for the table and safely pilot Das Boat downstream.

programme.title: Das Boat - Steven Rinella and Grant Gulley Troll for Lake Trout on Lake Michigan
programme.desc: Steve introduces you to Dos Boat. Steve gets to South Haven, MI, where he recruits the help of local charter captain Grant Gully. Steve, Grant, and a fabricator put in 10 hours of work getting the boat ready to fish for lake trout in 100 feet of water. Grant is somewhat skeptical boat‚ ability to handle the water of Lake Michigan. They discuss Jon Gary îSteve‚ fishing mentor and the original captain of Dos Boat‚ the young anglers Jon influenced, the decline (and comeback) of the lake trout.

programme.title: Das Boat - Au Sable River Trout with Janis Putelis and Brian Kozminski
programme.desc: Steve hauls Dos Boat to Boyne City, Michigan. Janis Putelis connects with trout fishing guide Brian Kozminski. They try to get the boat prepared for a nighttime river expedition by setting it up for rowing. Along the way they discuss: the history and fish of the Iconic Au Sable river, the giant hexagenia mayflies that hatch there, whether or not fish give a damn how pretty your cast is, the load of fishing options in Michigan, and the ability to pivot when conditions suck.

programme.title: Das Boat - Menominee River Smallmouth with Joe Cermele and Tim Landwehr
programme.desc: Dos Boat crosses the Straits of Mackinaw and heads west to the Wisconsin, U.P. border. Joe Cermele teams up Tim Landwehr. They burn Tim‚ home river on a fishing show. A proposed sulfide mine threatens the future of this fishery, and he wants you to know about it. Other topics discussed: finding big fish in skinny water, how delicious northern pike are, losing a bass but catching the ‚ follower, and a hell of a lot more.

programme.title: Das Boat - Northern Wisconsin Musky with Oliver Ngy and Kevin Harlander
programme.desc: Dos Boat meets up with Oliver Ngy and Kevin Harlander in North Central Wisconsin. Oliver and Kevin are here for two things: big musky and delicious panfish. They give Das Boat a lake fishing upgrade with electronics and a powerful trolling motor. They convert a cooler into a livewell to keep bait and fish alive. They discuss whether or not it really takes 10,000 casts to catch a musky, losing the fish of a lifetime right at the boat, the figure 8, how bluegills make you feel like a winner.

programme.title: Das Boat - Big Mouth Buffalo with Ryan Callaghan and Miles Nolte
programme.desc: Ryan Callaghan and Miles Nolte travel to Minnesota to try to catch big mouth buffalo. The guys build a raised casting platform on Das Boat. They meet Alec Lackmann, the world‚ foremost expert on big mouth buffalo. Cal and Miles tag along with Alec to help release some buffalo that he was studying. Cal and Miles head over to the Mississippi River to try their luck on a population of river buffalo that don't get hunted with bows.

programme.title: Das Boat - Freshwater Drum with Danielle Prewett and Frank Smethurst
programme.desc: In the Das Boat Season 2 finale, Danielle Prewett and fishing guide Frank Smethurst explore Red Lake, MN, targeting freshwater drum, a fish locals dismiss as a nuisance. With Texan Danielle's expertise in cooking redfish and a new boat upgrade by Minnesota guide Josh Desmit, they set out to prove the critics wrong.

programme.title: Das Boat - Skyline Stripers with Ryan Callaghan and Joe Cermele
programme.desc: Das Boat Northeast debuts in New Jersey, where Ryan Callaghan teams up with local Joe Cermele to target the economically vital striped bass. Before the hunt, they dedicate time to refurbishing their 1973 Mako, a major project turning decayed fiberglass into a functional vessel ready for the adventure ahead.

programme.title: Das Boat - The Bounty Of Old Barney
programme.desc: In this episode, Captain Frank Crescitelli andMeatEater's own Chef Jean-Paul Bourgeois get down and dirty in New Jersey's iconic Barnegat Bay. While their focus is exploring what happened tothe once flourishing weakfish population, they also spend time digging for clams, seining grass shrimp, and soaking greasy chicken parts for delicious blue crabs.

programme.title: Das Boat - Fish the Swamp!
programme.desc: In the unique waters of Washington DC, Chef Kevin Gillespie partners with seasoned kayak angler Kristine Fischer. Their mission: learn more about invasive species like blue catfish and snakehead in the Potomac River and its adjacent swamps. Beyond the thrill of the hunt, they delve into the ecological repercussions of these intruders. As they reel in their catch, they also explore the culinary potential, offering a multifaceted perspective on this unconventional fishing experience.

programme.title: Das Boat - Bow Hunting
programme.desc: Bowfin are a native species that rarely get the love they deserve. In this episode, bass phenom Oliver Ngy teams up with fly legend Blane Chocklett on Lake Champlain to get deep in the weeds on the importance of bowfin in the ecosystem. They'll also test their mettle against what can be a challenging fish that punishes tackle and fights to the death.

programme.title: MeatEater - Into the Clouds: Sitka Blacktail Deer
programme.desc: Steven Rinella charters a float plane to drop off on a remote lake in Alaska's coastal rainforest for a solo Sitka blacktail deer hunt. With challenging terrain, thick fog, and incessant rain, finding a buck won't be easy. But if Steve connects on a Sitka blacktail, he'll celebrate with a camp meal of rock-pounded tenderloin.

programme.title: MeatEater - The Sweetest Meat: Alaskan Black Bear
programme.desc: As summer turns to fall, Steve heads into the backcountry of Alaska's Chugach Range. The bears here are on a quest to fatten up on high elevation blueberries before they hibernate for the winter. Steve will need to hike into steep, rugged terrain to find a fat black bear and some of the finest tasting meat available to the American hunter.

programme.title: MeatEater - The Waters Edge: Waterfowl in Alaska
programme.desc: For a waterfowler's dream hunt, Steven Rinella joins his friend, wildlife biologist Brandt Meixell, on a remote trip to some untouched Alaska wetlands in search of ducks and geese. With a spread of decoys and a loyal retriever, they try to get their limit and fill their bellies with willow-spit roasted whole duck.

programme.title: MeatEater - The Rugged Peaks: Alaskan Mountain Goat
programme.desc: Every year, a handful of hunters draw a mountain goat permit to hunt the Mills Creek region of Alaska‚ Kenai Peninsula. Steven Rinella holds one of the permits this year, and he and his brother Danny backpack into the mountains, into rugged country they‚ never seen, in hopes of finding a billy goat.

programme.title: MeatEater - The New American Food Chain: Wild Pigs
programme.desc: On this trip, Steve travels to the Sacramento Valley in central California in search of a new challenge and seriously good food. 300 years ago Spanish settlers let a handful of pigs loose in order to turn acorns into bacon, and today Steve is hunting the feral descendants of those pigs. If he's successful in finding a wild boar, Steve will prepare a backcountry gourmet feast of pork loin roasted with apples and rosemary cooked in tin foil over a fire.
